{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_queenofspades_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608737/1958032801/1074.xml":{"full_text":"MIDTOWN NEW YORK\nBy ROBERT SYLVESTER\nJolly New Days\nNEW YORK.\u2014There a lot\not people still talking about the\ngood old days of show business,\nwhen the Palace was going\nstrong with two-a-day and\nvaudeville was cleaning up\nacross the country. But these\nare not the people who have\nkept up with the times; their\nfingers on the pulse of the na\ntion and such. There is one\ngentleman who did. however,\ndown through the years. His\nname is Jolly Joyce.\nHe broke into show business\n40 years ago as a comedian in\nChinese restaurants, billed as\n\u2022\u2022The Pat Boy of Joy.\u201d He read\nthe handwriting on the wall,\nthough, when he saw his em\nployers putting chow mein into\ncontainers, so he became an\nagent.\nNow his talent list sounds,\nlike a rock \u2019n\u2019 roll nightmare.\nIt includes Johnny Sparrow\nand His Bows and Arrows,\nTommy Reilly and His Tom\nCats. Five Sharps and a Plat,\nGeorgie Ross and His Red Tops,\nSteve Gibson and His Red\nCaps. Frankie Day and the\nKnights. Bill Haley and His\nComets.\nWhat does success mean to\nJolly?\n\u2022\u2022Well.\u201d he says, \"when I\nfirst came to New York and\nopened here, I stayed at the\nMills Hotel.\u201d\n\nOne of the unsolved mys-,\nteries of all time is the deep\nquestion of what a woman\ncarries around in her purse.\nWell, always on the alert to\nanswer such world shaking\nquestions, herewith is the re\nport of a recent survey taken\nby Fawcett Publications; \u201cOut\nof 100 women, 97 carry lip\nstick: 81 carry tissues; 70 in\nclude a compact; 53, perfume:\n30. eyebrow pencil; 22, hand\nlotion; 16. rouge; 14. mas\ncara: 11. makeup base; 10.\nlipstick brush: 5, a comb, and\n2 carry a nail file.\nAnd 99 per cent of the time,\nsays newscaster Art Van Horn,\nthe 15 cents for bus fare is on\nthe bottom of all this.\n\nCBS-Radio's Art Peck, who\nbroadcast the Sebring sports\ncar races reports, with regret,\nthat Ricardo Rodriguez. Mex\nico\u2019s leading sports car driver\nwho won several races in\nhis Porsche last year, did not\ncompete. Had Rodriguez ent\nered, he would have had to be\ndriven to the track.\nHe\u2019s 15 years old. Too young\nfor a driver\u2019s license.\n\nRobert Preston, making his\nsong-and-dance debut in \u201cThe\nMusic Man.\u201d received a caged,\ncanary as a good luck gift from\nhis pals, Philip Coolidge and\nFrank Maxwell. Attached to the\ncage was a note reading, \u201cDon\u2019t\nANN* ANTHONY ANTHONY\nMAGNANI-QUINN FRANCIOSA\nmuMm \"in m\nPLAYHOUSE <\u00bbl 1 7? is\n\u2014rarnsas\n*XPi,rss\u00a3\nwrist mssis* m- iswciit t> tnutm\ntmnnWy: tiiAioiiqot \u00abih tinri\u2019r\n2 NEW MAJOR JliS\nHE TURNED KILLER\nthe day he EHM\nalone...\nagainst the -MmYi\nmarauders!\nIFREDmIcMURRAY\nJOAN WELDON\nI JOHN ERICSON\nftfHfftsAi ummm kjww\nif\nHr\nmnTwts mm mws tt\u00bb toss\n10 DAYS IN A\nNATURE\nCAMP\u201d\nADMO ATTRACTION\nMENIAL BURLESQUE\nW GORGEOUS cot OR!\nI t Yv Hkcp-\nJust stand there\u2014sing some\nthing.\u201d\n\nFor what is probably the first\ntime in night club history, a\nclub has been forced to close\non Fridays, one of its best busi\nness nights, by a union\u2014and\nthere isn\u2019t any labor trouble\nInvolved. Arele\u2019s New Rou\nmanian, a kosher night club\nin Queens, has received orders\nfrom the Union of Orthodox\nRabbis to close the club on Fri\nday or lose the services of the\nrabbi who is posted in the\nkitchen nightly to supervise the\ncooking. So, from now on, the\nplace will be shut tight Friday\n\u2014a good rabbi nowadays is\nhard to find.\n\nOutside \u201c21\u201d the other night,\nRobert Q. Lewis hailed a cab,\nand on the way home, the\ndriver struck up a conversation.\n\u201cThat \u20182l\u2019 is a real swanky\njoint, ain\u2019t it?\u201d said the cabbie.\n\u201cI guess. What do you mean\nby swanky?\u201d Lewis asked.\n\u201cSwanky?\u201d said the driver.\n\"That\u2019s where the dames wear\nhats and the guys don\u2019t.\u201d\n\nAnd Alan King reports in\nwith the story of the fighter\ncomplaining \u201cI want to fight\nPunchy Plotkin!\u201d and the man\nager explaining, \u201cYou can\u2019t\nfight him. You are Punchy\nPlotkin.\u201d\nHOLLYWOOD\nContinued From Page A-22\nat the Oscar awards, the spot\nwas offered to Betty Hutton.\nBut Betty\u2019s agents said no. ex\nplaining, \"We don\u2019t consider\nthis important enough.\u201d\n\nBob Hope was sleepy when\nhe arrived in Hollywood from\nRussia. \u201cI took a pill to keep\nme asleep until nine, but the\nplane arrived at six,\u201d com\nplained Robert.\nJerry Wald, grateful for the\nstupendous turnout of stars for\nhis Oscar show, told me. \u201cI\u2019m\n'PeAiny,\n45-\nRESTAURANT\nNorthern CHing** Feed\nSine* 1947\nPopulor Prices Perty Facilities\n\u201cMEMBER DINERS CLUB**\n111 11th St. N.W. Ml. 1-2122\n5522 Gena. Avs. N.W. WO.l-lOTS\n*rea Dinner Parking at PIP IJtti N.W.\nw\u00bbiWaRIR W a 1\nI Lass Trade-In Allowance *2o\u00b0\u00b0 4\n1 *oT\nfl Jn\n9L tddi beiuty value to\nj ONLY 75c A WEEK I with Benrua^^^^j\nsis!. Rons: a\nCgns# Hdoy an* aa. Ihgaa naur 19*4 a* Bi*]:K\n\u2022annn wmchM. telod on* Wear II fa, 702 Ith SJrttl N.W. _ 1331 F SlfMt N.W.\n16 Aay\u00bb 1 yaw om not too rinsed ,hat (J&6(/&C4ZfL4-\nthis Is (ha mast tarrlde watch yav\u2019va\navav awraad. .etavn H lar a fuh nfwnd. 111 N Slrftl N.E. 1243 Gm 4 N*H 11 S.E.\n\n8\ngoing to break my neck for\nthese people.\u201d Until the last\nminute Jerry was hoping to get\nGarbo to accept officially on the\nPantages Theater stage the\nhonorary Oscar she won for a\n1954 foreign-language movie,\nbut took possession of only\nthree weeks ago.\nA London reporter described\nJeff Chandler\u2019s curly iron-gray\nhair-do as \u201ca crew-cut pot\nscourer.\u201d And when Jeff was\nasked why he had taken up\nsinging, he tartly retorted, \u201cNo\none asks Frank Sinatra why\nhe took up acting.\u201d\nThe story behind Polly Ber\ngen\u2019s adopted tot. Pamela:\nPolly and husband Freddie\nFields lost their expected baby\nlast year, after buying every\nthing that goes with an infant.\nNow Pam\u2014they call her P. K.\n\u2014is using them.\nSwitzerland appears to be\nthe only country in the world\nIN PERSON\nlouis m\nM SATCNNO\u201dLnr\nARMSTRONG\nAND HIS ALL STARS\nONLY WASHINGTON\nAPPEARANCE THIS SEASON\nULINE ARENA\nONE PERF. ONLY\nTHURS., APR. 10-4:30 P.M,\nArena Ploor:\nTiers: f 1.2&, 1.05, 2.30. 2.75. 3 30.\nBeats Now\u2014Mall Orders Accepted.\nHAYES CONCERT BUREAU\n1108 O St. N.W. rCamobeirs)\nNA. 8-7151 Steinway Plano\nwwNWWHivww^ifvvvmimi\nIltUiUpU\nSee the Academy\nm; +t>Jm Award Winning Performance\nJOANNE WOODWARD\n\u201cThe 3 Faces of Eve\u201d\nCO-STARRING DAVID WAYNE\u2014LEE J. COBB\nScout Executive\nGets Chicago Post\nHarold L. Rush. Washington\nScout executive, has resigned\nto take a similar post In Chi\ncago, the Boy Scouts\u2019 National\nCapital Area Council disclosed\ntoday.\nHis Midwestern appointment\nwill become effective on Sep\ntember 1. Mr. Rush's successor\nin Washington has not been\nchosen, an official said.\nA professional Scouter since\nholding out against the \u201csack\u201d\nlook, according to Swiss star\nLilo Pulver. \"We Swiss are\nconservative,\u201d writes Lilo. \u201cWe\ndon\u2019t like radical departures\nfrom the curves nature gave\nus.\u201d\nACADEMY AWARD WINNER\nQlec QumtuM\nM i- M Film Festival\nURNF*\u2019\u2019\u201d' fyMHN\ni NOW SHOWING\nALEC GUINNESS IN TWO Os MIS\n\u25a0v GREATEST SCREEN TRIUMPHS\n'THE PRISONER\"\n\"LAST HOLIDAY\"\nMATINEES DAILY AT I P.M.\n1933, Mr. Rush was a naval\nofficer In World War n. He\ncame to Washington in Jan\nuary, 1956. During his tenure\nthe NationaL Capital Area\nCouncil has grown from 34,000\nto 40,000 boys.\nHe was executive vice chair\nman of the General Services\ncommittee for the 1957 presi\ndential inaugural. He is a\nmember of Westmoreland Con\ngregational Church and the\nRotary Club of Washington.\nIn 1956 and 1957 he served\nas 